feedback_text: Hilarious and extremely helpful in term of explaining key components to build into platforms: both front end and back end. He has explained to me importance of setting up acessibility features and parameters, Priority matrix mapping, and I have seen him add this same value to others giving them insightful, unique information I have not heard other peers have the knowledge base to even consider or use the tech language. He is very intelligent. We joke around allot, but I truly respect his knowledge. I do not think his brilliance is showing in his work yet. His ideas are solid and with some more development can be really innovative.
summary:
Strengths: Hilarious and extremely helpful in explaining key components for platform development. Shares importance of accessibility features, parameters, and priority matrix mapping. Provides insightful and unique information to others.

Opportunities: Brilliance not fully reflected in current work. Ideas have potential for innovation with further development.

Additional Comments: Respect for his knowledge and intelligence shines through the feedback. Encouragement for continued growth and showcasing brilliance in work.

feedback_text: I was happy to come into class and see Sam had settled in on his MVP and had got to working on it.
